title: Clint Dempsey goes 30 minutes in preseason start
text:
Clint Dempsey goes 30 minutes in preseason start USA Today 0 Feb 4, 2017 9:20:42 PM The former U.S. national team captain returned to action with the Seattle Sounders Saturday night, putting in 30 minutes in a preseason start. 
Clint Dempsey started the Seattle Sounders' preseason match against the Portland Timbers Saturday night. 
The former U.S. national team captain has been out of action since August due to an irregular heart beat, but was lively in his first half-hour back on the field for the Sounders. 
Soccer kits for every NFL team 
The Sounders and Timbers faced off in Tucson, Arizona, with the match marking the opening of the preseason match schedule for Seattle. 
The Sounders will play a scrimmage against the San Jose Earthquakes Tuesday before moving on to the Carolina Challenge Cup. Related
